abstract: I still can’t talk about what happened to me because of a nondisclosure agreement.
snippet: I still can’t talk about what happened to me because of a nondisclosure agreement.
lead_paragraph: When my retaliation and sexual harassment complaint against Roger Ailes, the former Fox News chairman and C.E.O., went public in 2016, there were no #MeToo or Times Up movements to help rally support for my cause. In the years that followed, many more women have found the courage to come forward, calling out Bill O’Reilly, Matt Lauer, Charlie Rose, Harvey Weinstein and other powerful men accused of abusing their power. When I sued, I could have never known that my story and the stories of other women at Fox would turn into both a television mini-series and a film, and, more important, that I would be prohibited from speaking about these projects.

abstract: The legislation underscores an unyielding stream of bipartisan rage at Turkey.
snippet: The legislation underscores an unyielding stream of bipartisan rage at Turkey.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate voted unanimously on Thursday to recognize the Armenian genocide as a matter of American foreign policy, a move that was made over the objections of the Trump administration and that underscored lawmakers’ bipartisan rage at Turkey.

abstract: A hearing in Virginia was the first time a full appeals panel has considered the anticorruption clauses of the Constitution.
snippet: A hearing in Virginia was the first time a full appeals panel has considered the anticorruption clauses of the Constitution.
lead_paragraph: RICHMOND, Va. — A federal appeals court in Virginia heard arguments Thursday about whether to revive a lawsuit accusing President Trump of violating the Constitution by profiting from his hotel near the White House, in a spirited session that indicated sharp divisions among the judges over the legal consequences of the president’s conduct.

abstract: President Donald Trump’s reelection campaign on Thursday shrugged off the president's expected impeachment less than a year before Election Day, talking up the campaign's data collection efforts and declaring that no one in the Democratic field can compete with the incumbent.
snippet: President Donald Trump’s reelection campaign on Thursday shrugged off the president's expected impeachment less than a year before Election Day, talking up the campaign's data collection efforts and declaring that no one in the Democratic field ca...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump’s reelection campaign on Thursday shrugged off the president's expected impeachment less than a year before Election Day, talking up the campaign's data collection efforts and declaring that no one in the Democratic field can compete with the incumbent.
headline_main: Playing Down Impeachment, Trump Campaign Voices Confidence
headline_print_headline: Playing Down Impeachment, Trump Campaign Voices Confidence

abstract: The education secretary said “many students” got “a valuable education” from for-profit colleges as officials planned a round of notifications to applicants for full relief, 95 percent denials.
snippet: The education secretary said “many students” got “a valuable education” from for-profit colleges as officials planned a round of notifications to applicants for full relief, 95 percent denials.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Education Secretary Betsy DeVos on Thursday vigorously defended her decision to grant partial or no loan relief to tens of thousands of students who were misled by for-profit colleges, blaming the Obama administration for overpromising debt relief.
